# Wavefront OBJ Format Basics

## Overview
OBJ is a plain-text 3D geometry format. Key line prefixes:

| Prefix | Meaning                        |
|--------|--------------------------------|
| "'`v`    | Vertex position (x y z)       |
| `vt`   | Texture coordinate (u v)      |
| `vn`   | Vertex normal (nx ny nz)      |
| `f`    | Face (1-based vertex indices)  |
| `o`    | Object name                    |

## Face Index Formats
- `f v1 v2 v3` — position only
- `f v1/vt1 v2/vt2 v3/vt3` — position + UV
- `f v1/vt1/vn1 v2/vt2/vn2 v3/vt3/vn3` — position + UV + normal
- `f v1//vn1 v2//vn2 v3//vn3` — position + normal (no UV)

## Coordinate System
OBJ has no inherent up-axis. Blender imports OBJ assuming **Z-up** by default.
Three.js is **Y-up**. A −90° X rotation converts Y-up → Z-up.

## Validation
- Vertex count: `grep -c '"'"'^v '"' file.obj"'`
- Face count: `grep -c '"'"'^f '"' file.obj"'`
